pullRequest.body:
Definitions and basic properties of non-unital star subsemirings

---

This file heavily copies `Mathlib.Algebra.Star.NonUnitalSubalgebra`, so I'm happy to assign the copyright to @j-loreaux if that's the appropriate thing to do.

So far I've mostly only developed what's required for #6595 - I thought I'd check that this was the right approach before going further.

I think we don't want `StarSubset`, unless you have an explicit application in mind. Also, it would be nice if the unital versions of all these were placed in a separate file.
bors d+
I'm dubious that we want this. Do you have applications in mind for sets that are closed *only* under the `star` operation?
No application in mind at present. Originally I was thinking there might be some efficiency in having a common base class, but I'm not convinced that's actually the case, so I have removed it now.

At the very least, the capitalization is wrong, but also, I think we should match naming with `Subsemigroup`. If we want to switch the naming of both to `Magma`, then fine, but that should be a separate PR.
```suggestion
/-- A sub star magma is a subset of a magma which is closed under the `star`-/
structure SubStarSemigroup (M : Type v) [Mul M] [Star M] extends Subsemigroup M, StarSubset M : Type v
```
Possibly I should have used  `NonAssocSemigroup` in #7060 instead of `Magma` for consistency with `(NonUnital)NonAssoc(Semi)ring`?
I've renamed `SubStarmagma` as `SubStarSemigroup`.
It's weird that this is in the `NonUnitalSubsemiring` file. Perhaps you can move the unital stuff out of here into a separate file (and possibly even a separate PR).
I've moved `StarSubsemiring` into `Algebra/Star/Subsemiring`.

associativity, or the lack thereof, mostly comes from the ambient ring.
```suggestion
/-- A non-unital star subsemiring is a non-unital subsemiring which also is closed under the
`star` operation. -/
```

```suggestion
/-- Copy of a non-unital star subsemiring with a new `carrier` equal to the old one.
```

```suggestion
/-- The center of a non-unital non-associative semiring `R` is the set of elements that
commute and associate with everything in `R`, here realized as non-unital star 
subsemiring. -/
def center (R) [NonUnitalNonAssocSemiring R] [StarRing R] : NonUnitalStarSubsemiring R where
```

```suggestion
/-- The center of magma `A` is the set of elements that commute and associate
with everything in `A`, here realized as a `SubStarSemigroup`. -/
```

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion commute and associate with everything in `R`, here realized as non-unital star ```

```suggestion
-- this uses the `Star` instance `s` inherits from `StarMemClass (StarSubsemiring R A) A`
```
